com.bluegosling.collections.queues

Interface PriorityQueue.Entry<E,P>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of element in this queue entry
    P - the type of the priority associated with each element
    Enclosing interface:
    PriorityQueue<E,P>

    public static interface PriorityQueue.Entry<E,P>
    An entry in a priority queue. This represents an element in the queue and its associated priority.

        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the queue does not support this type of change (some queues, for example, may not allow increasing the priority, only decreasing)

      • equals

        boolean equals(Object o)

      • hashCode

        int hashCode()
        Computes the hash code for this entry. The entry's hash code is computed as priority.hashCode() ^ element.hashCode(). If either priority or element is null then its hash code is considered to be zero.
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class Object
        Returns:
        the has code for this entry, computed as described above
